<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.156/27a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mooney</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-26T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                        1919—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s despatches February 14, 20, and March 12,<note n="6" xml:id="d386fn6">None printed.</note> regarding extension
                            concession Construction and Engineering Finance Company, you are
                            instructed to cooperate with representative of Company in Paraguay in
                            presenting matter to Paraguayan Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>